Wash and dry produce. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place potatoes
in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil
and cook until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to the
pot. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth; season with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

While potatoes cook, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon},
@?sugar{1%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and toss
to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @katsu sauce{4%tablespoon} and
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Refrigerate slaw and katsu mayo until ready to serve.

== Beef Mixture ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large heavy-bottomed pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and
@soy sauce{2%tablespoon}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Carefully drain any excess grease from pan.

Add beef mixture, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, and 2 TBSP reserved potato
cooking liquid to pot with potatoes; stir to combine. Taste and season with
salt and pepper if desired.

> TIP: If mixture seems too crumbly, add more reserved potato cooking liquid
> a splash at a time until a moldable consistency is achieved.

Wash and dry pan.

== Breading ==

In a #shallow dish{}, combine @flour{2%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{}.

In a separate shallow dish, whisk together @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and
@water{1.5%tablespoon}.

Place remaining @panko breadcrumbs{3/4%cup} in a third shallow dish.

== Forming Croquettes ==

Once cool enough to handle, form croquette mixture into four 1-inch-thick
patties. (For less mess, wear food-safe gloves or lightly coat your hands with
oil before forming the patties.)

> TIP: Double the number of patties if you prefer a smaller croquette!

Working one at a time, gently press patties into flour until fully coated.
Gently tap off excess, then dip both sides into sour cream mixture. Let excess
drip off, then press into panko until fully coated.

== Frying ==

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in pan used for beef over medium-high
heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of flour sizzles immediately when
added to the pan, add coated patties. Cook until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}
per side.

> TIP: Fry in batches if necessary; lower heat if patties begin to brown too
> quickly.

Transfer croquettes to a #paper-towel-lined plate{} and immediately season with
salt.

== To Serve ==

Divide croquettes and slaw between plates in separate sections. Serve with katsu
mayo on the side for dipping.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.